HEADWORD: Artemisia
<hw>Ar`te*mi"si*a</hw> <pr>(⟦aum⟧rt⟦esl⟧"m⟦icr⟧zh"⟦icr⟧*⟦adot⟧
<it>or</it> ⟦aum⟧rt⟦esl⟧"m⟦icr⟧sh"⟦icr⟧*⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>Artemisia</ets>, Gr. <grk>'Artemisi`a</grk>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of plants including the plants called
mugwort, southernwood, and wormwood. Of these <spn>Artemisia
absinthium</spn>, or common wormwood, is well known, and <spn>Artemisia
tridentata</spn> is the sage brush of the Rocky Mountain
region.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>arteria</ent>⟦br⟧
